ment Board. 

Senator NELSON. Mr. Chairman, is that a vote? 
Senator DORGAN. Yes. 
Senator NELSON. Well, then I’ll just conclude by saying that, you 
know,  one  of  the  phoniest  problems  that  we  have,  over  and  over, 
is  the  question  of  disability  for  veterans.  And  they  go  through  all 
of  these  disability  claims  procedures  that  are  quite  extensive. 
Maybe  we  ought  to  take  a  lesson  from  the  experience  that  we  try 
to  determine  the  degree  of  disability  with  our  veterans  and  have 
that be a lesson to apply here. 

Thank you. 
Senator DORGAN. Senator Nelson, thank you very much. 
A  vote  did  start  at  12,  noon,  and  I  would  normally  ask  if  we 
could  stand  in  recess,  but,  because  there  is  a  vote  following  this, 
it would require at least a half-hour recess, and I don’t want to in-
convenience  you.  All  of  you  who  have  testified  today  have  come 
here  and  provided,  I  think,  some  real  assistance  in  giving  us  your 
