sional sport and are now living in poverty, are now living in a cir-
cumstance  where  they  can’t  find  the  kind  of  healthcare  that  they 
need, or the kind of medical assistance they need. 

We  will  certainly  evaluate  the  testimony  and  try  to  consider 
what kinds of things might be available. And I think, Mr. Commis-
sioner  and  Mr.  Upshaw,  you,  I  hope,  will  take  a  look.  What  I’m 

